<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 7:22PM MDT  by NWS RapidCity</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Custer
County through 745 PM MDT...
At 722 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles west of Hermosa, or 15 miles south of Rapid City, moving
southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Hermosa around 725 PM MDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
